{
  "texts": [
    "First, NLP combined with traditional machine learning like SVM (Long et al., 2019), LightGBM (Wu et al., 2020), XGBoost and RF (Jourovski et al., 2020; Petropoulos and Siakoulis, 2021).",
    "Evidence supports that financial news or social media information can provide an additional advantage in predicting price or market turbulence trends.",
    "This approach often entails constructing numerous features before inputting them into the ML model.",
    "Alternatively, some studies explore DL techniques, which can automatically extract features from news or social media.",
    "For instance, a self-regulated generative adversarial network was proposed to enhance generalization and overcome stochasticity in predicting stock movements based on financial news and historical price data (Xu et al., 2022)."
  ]
}